05/02/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- German Interior Minister Wolfgang Schaeuble expressed his support on Monday (February 4th) for Turkey's fight against terrorism, during a visit to Ankara where he met with counterpart, Beshir Atalay. 
Schaeuble and Atalay discussed global terrorism issues and the branches and activities of terrorist organisations. 
Atalay reiterated Turkey's right to fight the Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) and said Ankara expects more help from Germany in its efforts. 
Schaeuble, for his part, said Berlin will boost information exchanges with Ankara and will better analyse PKK data and efforts to curb its activities.
Meanwhile, Turkish Justice Minister Mehmet Ali Sahin asked German authorities to conduct a thorough investigation into the cause of a deadly fire in the German town of Ludwigshafen. 
The blaze, Monday morning, roared though a building in which two dozen Turkish families lived. 
Nine people were killed, including five children. 
Nearly 60 other Turkish nationals were injured. 
(Hurriyet, Radikal, Zaman, Milliyet, Sabah - 05/02/08; Anadolu news agency, NTV, The Press Association, AP, UPI, Bloomberg, DPA, ANKA, Trend - 04/02/08)
